    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix DL_TTI.request packing/unpacking for group PDU indexing\n\n### Summary\nThe nfapi P7 packing/unpacking routines for DL_TTI.request messages had two critical issues causing cross-layer parameter mismatches between PHY, MAC, and RRC layers. \n\nFirst, in `pack_dl_tti_request()`, a misplaced early return statement caused only the first UE group to be processed, leading to incomplete DL scheduling. Second, in `unpack_dl_tti_request()`, the group PDU index arrays were incorrectly handled during deserialization, causing memory corruption and inconsistent UE-specific parameter propagation.\n\nThese issues manifested as RRC connection failures and random access failures during initial access procedures, particularly affecting UEs with multiple PDU groups. The gNB would send malformed DL assignments, causing UEs to fail MAC CE processing and eventually RRC connection release.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Removed erroneous early return in `pack_dl_tti_request()` loop\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Fixed PDU index array unpacking logic in `unpack_dl_tti_request()`\n"
}